      • whereQualifiedNameStartsWith

        public static co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch._types.query_dsl.Query whereQualifiedNameStartsWith​(java.lang.String qualifiedName)
        Returns a query that will only match assets with a qualifiedName that begins with the provided string. This is useful for finding all assets within a particular parent asset, such as all tables, views, and columns within a schema (when the provided qualifiedName is for a schema).
        Parameters:
        qualifiedName - for the parent asset in which to find all child assets
        Returns:
        a query that will only match assets with a qualifiedName that begins with the provided string

      • withAtLeastOneClassification

        public static co.elastic.clients.elasticsearch._types.query_dsl.Query withAtLeastOneClassification​(java.util.List<java.lang.String> classificationNames)
                                                                                            throws AtlanException
        Returns a query that will only match assets that have at least one of the classifications provided. This will match irrespective of the classification being directly applied to the asset, or if it was propagated to the asset.
        Parameters:
        classificationNames - human-readable names of the classifications
        Returns:
        a query that will only match assets that have at least one of the classifications provided
        Throws:
        AtlanException - on any error communicating with the API to refresh the classification cache
